subSubSection.paragraph:
This species differs from
C. parvirostris
by its bent rostrum with fewer dorsal teeth (0 – 5) (vs bent rostrum with 8 – 10 dorsal teeth in
C. parvirostris
) and its P2 carpus shorter 4.2 – 5.2 times as long as wide (vs 6.0 – 7.4 in
C. parvirostris
) and so is P2 chela 2.0 – 2.7 times as long as wide (vs 2.6 – 3.0 in
C. parvirostris
).
